description._content: Description: Mosaics on North wall of the Nave. (Plate 10 from "The Church of the Nativity at Bethlehem", by W. Harvey, W.R. Lethaby, O.M. Dalton, H.A.A. Cruso and A.C. Headlam, Batsford, on behalf of the Bysantine Research Fund, London 1910). Location: Bethlehem, Palestine Date: 1910 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/737 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown. We have attempted to provide place information for the images automatically but our software may not have found the correct location.
